42:42.132 --> 42:44.396
You can't stay here, Jerry.

42:47.137 --> 42:49.332
You're nuts.

42:49.439 --> 42:50.565
Why?

42:52.609 --> 42:54.338
Because it's free.

42:57.147 --> 42:58.876
I don't need your charity, Audrey.

42:58.982 --> 43:03.112
Who's offering you charity?
I'm the one that needs the help here.

43:04.454 --> 43:07.787
Really, you know
how high my mortgage is?

43:07.924 --> 43:10.051
You can move in, get yourself situated,

43:10.160 --> 43:13.891
and, eventually, you can get a job
and you can pay me rent.

43:27.177 --> 43:29.907
So how come
Brian never mentioned you?

43:31.348 --> 43:34.715
'Cause I'm a recovering heroin addict,
maybe?

43:46.697 --> 43:48.324
I hate my wife.

43:50.534 --> 43:52.798
I mean, since we're sharing.

43:54.271 --> 43:56.432
I hate everything about her.

43:57.374 --> 44:01.310
And she is gonna be furious when
she finds out I gave this shit to you.

44:01.445 --> 44:02.571
Okay.

44:20.363 --> 44:21.591
-Hey, Dory.
-Hi.

44:21.698 --> 44:24.496
You gonna give us a hand? Okay, cool.

44:30.907 --> 44:32.272
Hey, Dory.

44:37.347 --> 44:38.712
You got it?

44:40.417 --> 44:44.649
-There we go.
-Good job, good job. Good job.

44:53.764 --> 44:55.698
Yeah? Come in.

44:59.603 --> 45:01.298
It's dinnertime.

45:03.507 --> 45:04.997
-Dinnertime?
-Yeah.

45:05.108 --> 45:07.076
My mom wanted me to come over
and get you.

45:07.210 --> 45:08.199
Okay.

45:09.613 --> 45:13.481
I need to put on my soles.

45:13.583 --> 45:18.816
I got two soles, one and two.

45:20.257 --> 45:22.054
Okay, let's do it.

45:29.065 --> 45:30.657
-Come on, that would be so cool!
-Yeah.

45:30.767 --> 45:33.065
-Yeah, that is so funny.
-Yeah.

45:33.203 --> 45:34.363
-Hey, Jerry.
-How you doing?

45:34.471 --> 45:37.099
Come on in. Have a seat.

45:37.240 --> 45:40.539
Girls? Girls, this is Jerry.

45:40.644 --> 45:42.737
-Jerry, this is Emily.
-Hi, Emily.

45:42.879 --> 45:44.904
-And this is Sarah.
-Hi, Sarah.

45:45.048 --> 45:48.882
And Jerry is a really good friend
of our family

45:48.985 --> 45:51.078
who's gonna have dinner
with us tonight, okay?

45:51.221 --> 45:52.210
So, who wants chicken?

45:52.322 --> 45:53.550
-Oh, me!
-Yeah?

45:53.657 --> 45:56.558
-Chicken. Jerry?
-No, I'm a vegetarian.

45:56.660 --> 45:58.355
You are? So am I.

45:58.461 --> 45:59.758
-Meat is murder.
-I want chicken.

45:59.896 --> 46:02.888
I'm gonna give it to you right now,
darling. There you go, one for you.

46:02.999 --> 46:05.092
So, I've been to California. Have you?

46:05.235 --> 46:08.727
Really? I haven't been to California,
but I hear it's really, really cool.

46:08.839 --> 46:11.205
-Yeah.
-I've always wanted to go there.

46:11.308 --> 46:12.570
It's really hot in the summer.

46:12.676 --> 46:17.807
Like, I was there in short-sleeve shirts
and shorts all the time. It was so hot.

46:17.948 --> 46:19.813
<i>-That is so cool.
-And it was so... Yeah.</i>

47:18.508 --> 47:19.668
Hey.

47:21.678 --> 47:23.043
Hey, Jerry!

47:25.015 --> 47:26.141
Yeah?

47:26.549 --> 47:28.210
I used to run with Brian every...

47:28.351 --> 47:31.218
I used to run with Brian every morning.

47:33.556 --> 47:36.354
So you want to go for a run?

47:40.096 --> 47:43.156
I mean, I'm smoking, Howard.

47:46.069 --> 47:47.468
I'll wait.

47:47.570 --> 47:51.165
Howard, I haven't ran
since junior high school.

47:51.274 --> 47:52.969
We'll just, you know,
go for however long.

47:53.076 --> 47:55.340
You know,
down to the driveway, whatever.

47:55.445 --> 47:57.640
We'll just go, you know?

47:57.781 --> 48:01.080
-I don't know if I can do it.
-We'll just go slow.

48:05.255 --> 48:09.089
That's it. That's it. Can't do it.

48:09.259 --> 48:10.419
Okay.

48:25.475 --> 48:27.238
This was our route.

48:30.480 --> 48:33.108
Thought about changing it afterward,

48:36.052 --> 48:38.179
but this is our route.

48:44.761 --> 48:48.219
Audrey, I don't think
she's facing reality, man.

48:50.934 --> 48:53.425
Is she gonna have to get a job?

48:53.570 --> 48:55.128
Who told you that?

48:55.271 --> 48:59.230
No. Brian was a great developer.

48:59.342 --> 49:02.106
He really thought outside the box,
you know? Great at rehabbing space.

49:02.245 --> 49:05.578
Found opportunities
where nobody else could. Was just...

49:05.682 --> 49:08.082
Their house? Paid off long ago.

49:08.651 --> 49:12.485
No, Audrey'll never have to worry
about money.

49:19.129 --> 49:21.256
-Morning.
-Hey.

49:21.364 --> 49:23.958
-Can I have some water?
-Yeah.

49:25.101 --> 49:26.591
Thank you.

49:40.116 --> 49:41.276
So...

49:52.195 --> 49:53.685
Why am I here?

50:07.677 --> 50:09.474
I don't really know.

50:20.557 --> 50:23.287
You know, it should've been you, Jerry.

50:29.232 --> 50:30.961
Why wasn't it you?

50:59.562 --> 51:02.588
-Sonics suck.
-You suck.

51:02.732 --> 51:04.723
It's a rebuilding year.

51:06.136 --> 51:07.603
What?

51:07.737 --> 51:09.261
"Rebuilding year?"

51:09.405 --> 51:11.100
-You're nine.
-Ten.

51:11.241 --> 51:12.674
And I'd take you down
on the court anytime.

51:12.775 --> 51:14.834
Oh, yeah? Go ahead.

51:18.615 --> 51:22.210
One more time, one more time,
one more time. Shoot it. Shoot it.

51:24.721 --> 51:26.052
Check.

51:27.557 --> 51:29.115
Come on, check.

51:30.093 --> 51:33.187
Do you ever feel
like you're inside of a movie?

51:33.596 --> 51:36.258
Do I ever feel like I'm inside a movie?

51:36.666 --> 51:37.758
No.

51:39.936 --> 51:41.597
It's a sad movie.

51:47.577 --> 51:49.977
You know, it'll change, Harp.

51:53.650 --> 51:54.981
I promise.

51:58.354 --> 52:00.652
Promise. Give me a high-five.

52:03.026 --> 52:04.152
Okay.

52:05.094 --> 52:06.755
The hook, the hook!
You gotta do the hook.

52:06.863 --> 52:09.127
Do the hook. Do the hook.

52:52.742 --> 52:54.710
And I'm...

52:56.312 --> 53:00.772
I'm wondering if maybe you might
be able to help me do something.

53:01.985 --> 53:03.111
Sure.

53:05.421 --> 53:06.718
Sleep.

53:08.558 --> 53:10.492
-I need to sleep.
-Sure.

53:24.040 --> 53:26.406
Okay, leave your shoes out here.

53:31.114 --> 53:33.514
And shut the door.

53:39.555 --> 53:40.681
Okay.

53:41.357 --> 53:42.585
Come on.

53:44.127 --> 53:46.493
-Okay.
-I need to sleep.

53:49.565 --> 53:52.898
-I don't know about this.
-No, trust me.

53:53.036 --> 53:55.698
This used to work better than Ambien.

53:57.440 --> 53:58.600
Okay.

53:59.742 --> 54:05.203
Bring this knee up, like that. Higher.
Yeah, that's it.

54:08.618 --> 54:10.381
Turn off the light.

54:14.957 --> 54:18.518
Okay, now... Now take your hand

54:21.497 --> 54:24.364
and pull down on the earlobe.

54:25.501 --> 54:29.130
Just pull down. Yeah, just like that.

54:30.340 --> 54:34.140
Yeah, but do it faster. Harder.

54:36.579 --> 54:37.603
Yeah.

54:37.747 --> 54:39.715
-Like that?
-That's it.

54:41.117 --> 54:42.948
Just keep doing that.

54:54.130 --> 54:56.792
I'm still awake. You gotta keep going.

54:59.635 --> 55:02.399
-Keep going, keep going.
-Okay, okay, okay.

55:02.505 --> 55:03.904
Keep going.

56:00.696 --> 56:04.029
Just for today,
my thoughts will be on my recovery.

56:04.167 --> 56:07.568
Living and enjoying life
without the use of drugs.

56:07.703 --> 56:11.002
Just for today,
I will have faith in someone in N.A.

56:11.107 --> 56:14.702
Who believes in me
and wants to help me in my recovery.

56:14.844 --> 56:16.539
Just for today, through N.A.,

56:16.679 --> 56:19.910
I will try to get
a better perspective on my life.

56:20.049 --> 56:22.244
Just for today, I will be unafraid.

56:22.385 --> 56:25.218
My thoughts will be
on my new associations,

56:25.354 --> 56:27.083
people who are not using

56:27.223 --> 56:29.350
and who have found a new way of life.

56:29.459 --> 56:33.088
So long as I follow that way,
I have nothing to fear.

56:34.797 --> 56:37.561
Is there anyone else
that'd like to share?

56:38.734 --> 56:40.201
-Okay.
-Yeah?

56:41.737 --> 56:43.932
Hi, my name is Jerry and I'm an addict.

56:44.073 --> 56:45.438
-Hi, Jerry.
-Hi, Jerry.

56:45.575 --> 56:47.770
I've been clean for 21 days.

56:48.945 --> 56:52.039
I'm here because my friend died.

56:52.148 --> 56:53.843
He wasn't a user.

56:54.951 --> 56:56.680
I knew him since second grade,

56:56.786 --> 57:00.586
and he was the only person
who never, ever gave up on me.

57:00.723 --> 57:04.250
He died a hero in this fucked-up,
tragic way.

57:07.497 --> 57:09.021
It killed me.

57:10.399 --> 57:11.957
It really did.

57:21.644 --> 57:23.544
-Jerry?
-Yeah?

57:23.646 --> 57:25.113
-Hey.
-Kelly.

57:27.083 --> 57:28.744
I liked your share tonight.

57:28.851 --> 57:31.979
Good. I like compliments. Thank you.

57:32.121 --> 57:34.988
-So 21 days, huh?
-Yeah.

57:35.124 --> 57:38.218
-Bouncing off the bottom.
-That's right, yeah.

57:41.464 --> 57:44.627
You should stay till the Serenity Prayer.

57:44.767 --> 57:46.064
-Excuse me?
-Well, last week you left

57:46.168 --> 57:49.899
before the Serenity Prayer,
and it's disrespectful to leave before it.

57:50.006 --> 57:51.837
Disrespectful to who?

57:53.442 --> 57:55.103
To your recovery.

57:56.879 --> 57:59.404
Well, my recovery thanks you.

58:06.122 --> 58:08.784
-Are you married?
-No.

58:11.494 --> 58:13.621
Do you have children?

58:13.729 --> 58:15.754
Do I have children? Two.

58:16.165 --> 58:19.293
A six-year-old son
and a 10-year-old daughter.

58:21.637 --> 58:25.801
Well, I should probably go,

58:25.908 --> 58:29.036
but I'll see you next week.

58:29.178 --> 58:30.304
Yeah.

58:31.814 --> 58:33.145
Buckle up!

58:41.390 --> 58:43.790
-Hey. Hi.
-Hi. Hey.

58:45.194 --> 58:48.220
You hungry? You want me
to make you a sandwich or...

58:48.364 --> 58:52.164
No, no, I'm fine.
You think I could use the computer?

58:53.536 --> 58:55.299
Yeah. Sure.

58:55.404 --> 58:58.202
Howard wants me
to look into something.

58:58.341 --> 59:00.707
Okay. Come on, I'll show you.

59:04.513 --> 59:06.003
It's in there.

01:00:00.734 --> 01:00:05.034
I know I should...
I think I need to clean it out or...

