01:27:54.506 --> 01:27:56.906
Do you want a little taste? Huh?

01:27:57.776 --> 01:27:59.539
When can I see him?

01:28:03.148 --> 01:28:06.379
Very soon, honey. Promise.

01:28:13.691 --> 01:28:15.215
All right. Come on, right here, man.

01:28:15.326 --> 01:28:17.988
Take this. Take this.
It's gonna help you out.

01:28:19.631 --> 01:28:22.725
All right, get it down, get it down.

01:28:22.834 --> 01:28:25.064
A little water. All right.

01:28:34.212 --> 01:28:35.577
I'm cold!

01:29:28.766 --> 01:29:31.132
Are you gonna die like my dad?

01:29:31.936 --> 01:29:33.130
Yeah.

01:29:35.340 --> 01:29:36.864
When?

01:29:37.008 --> 01:29:39.670
As soon as possible, I hope.

01:29:40.912 --> 01:29:42.903
You're kidding, right?

01:29:51.923 --> 01:29:54.585
I brought you some cookies and water.

01:29:55.527 --> 01:29:58.496
C-3PO and R2-D2.

01:29:58.596 --> 01:29:59.722
Yeah.

01:30:01.065 --> 01:30:04.034
3PO was a little stuck-up.

01:30:04.135 --> 01:30:05.227
Yeah.

01:30:05.370 --> 01:30:07.429
I like R2-D2 better.

01:30:09.574 --> 01:30:10.563
Excuse me.

01:30:12.810 --> 01:30:15.074
He seemed more accessible.

01:30:17.415 --> 01:30:18.677
Here.

01:30:38.303 --> 01:30:39.361
Here! Get back.

01:30:39.470 --> 01:30:40.596
Hey, Jerry.

01:30:42.307 --> 01:30:44.434
-Hi, Audrey.
-Ready, Emily?

01:30:44.576 --> 01:30:45.702
Come on in.

01:30:45.810 --> 01:30:48.142
I'm just... I'm smoking.

01:30:48.279 --> 01:30:51.146
Well, it's okay, you can smoke inside.

01:30:51.282 --> 01:30:52.476
Okay.

01:30:52.750 --> 01:30:55.617
So he does not pay, right?

01:30:56.588 --> 01:30:58.579
So, essentially, we are...

01:31:05.196 --> 01:31:06.754
-Hi, Diane.
-Hi!

01:31:06.864 --> 01:31:07.990
Hi.

01:31:10.001 --> 01:31:12.799
-How you doing?
-Feeling better.

01:31:14.939 --> 01:31:16.839
Good. You look better.

01:31:16.975 --> 01:31:18.272
Thanks.

01:31:22.547 --> 01:31:23.980
He's so wrong.

01:31:25.717 --> 01:31:26.911
What?

01:31:28.219 --> 01:31:31.780
"R2-D2 is more accessible?"

01:31:38.563 --> 01:31:41.157
So it wasn't a hallucination, huh?

01:31:41.299 --> 01:31:43.631
No. That was my son.

01:31:47.572 --> 01:31:50.837
He was so cute.
Brought me a cookie and water.

01:31:56.014 --> 01:31:57.777
Hold on, excuse me.

01:31:59.217 --> 01:32:01.378
Dory! What did your mother say?

01:32:01.519 --> 01:32:03.885
What did your mother say?
What did your mother say?

01:32:08.259 --> 01:32:10.659
You wanna sit and have some dinner?

01:32:10.762 --> 01:32:14.493
I think you should eat, you know?
Maybe you can keep it down.

01:32:14.599 --> 01:32:15.896
I'll try.

01:32:29.414 --> 01:32:31.143
See how he's spinning around like that?

01:32:31.249 --> 01:32:32.477
Brian used to do the same thing.

01:32:32.583 --> 01:32:35.074
Basketball games,
soccer games, any game.

01:32:35.219 --> 01:32:36.413
I know.

01:32:41.959 --> 01:32:43.824
I miss the silliness,

01:32:47.432 --> 01:32:48.763
the fun.

01:32:56.441 --> 01:33:01.174
I don't know if I'm ever gonna feel
happy again.

01:33:07.318 --> 01:33:10.219
Am I ever gonna feel beautiful?

01:33:10.321 --> 01:33:12.118
You are beautiful.

01:33:15.126 --> 01:33:17.253
No, I mean on the inside.

01:33:20.064 --> 01:33:23.261
You're the most beautiful woman
I've ever seen.

01:33:34.345 --> 01:33:35.903
-Hey.
-Hey.

01:33:36.814 --> 01:33:38.611
What are you doing here?

01:33:38.750 --> 01:33:40.377
I invited her.

01:33:50.828 --> 01:33:51.954
-Howard?
-Yeah?

01:33:52.096 --> 01:33:54.087
Can we swim in the pool tomorrow?

01:33:56.300 --> 01:33:59.792
I'm sorry, Dory,
but I don't live there anymore.

01:33:59.937 --> 01:34:00.961
Why?

01:34:01.105 --> 01:34:06.236
Well, because my soon to be ex-wife is
gonna get the house.

01:34:07.545 --> 01:34:10.810
Honey, we'll find another place to swim.
Okay?

01:34:10.948 --> 01:34:12.438
What kind of music
did your husband like?

01:34:12.550 --> 01:34:14.814
Did he like classical music?

01:34:19.290 --> 01:34:20.416
Yeah.

01:34:21.559 --> 01:34:23.925
What did he drink after dinner?

01:34:25.396 --> 01:34:28.297
Coffee? Italian wine? Or nothing?

01:34:33.237 --> 01:34:37.196
Chocolate milk.
He loved chocolate milk.

01:34:41.245 --> 01:34:44.043
-What kind of toothpaste did he use?
-Crest.

01:34:46.818 --> 01:34:48.285
He... Crest.

01:34:51.022 --> 01:34:54.014
Come on, ask me a question, Kelly.

01:34:54.158 --> 01:34:57.321
Okay, what was his favorite movie?

01:34:58.396 --> 01:35:00.057
I can't remember.

01:35:00.531 --> 01:35:04.695
<i>He liked this really old boring one,
with the guy from Meet the Fockers.</i>

01:35:06.270 --> 01:35:07.567
<i>Godfather II.</i>

01:35:07.705 --> 01:35:09.366
-It was One, actually.
-Yeah.

01:35:09.507 --> 01:35:10.496
No, he liked Two.

01:35:10.608 --> 01:35:11.836
My dad shot a squirrel.

01:35:11.943 --> 01:35:13.672
-He did?
-Yeah.

01:35:13.778 --> 01:35:16.838
He killed it. He cried a lot.

01:35:18.416 --> 01:35:20.145
He was nine.

01:35:20.251 --> 01:35:22.742
-We had a fire.
-You did?

01:35:22.887 --> 01:35:24.912
Yeah.

01:35:25.056 --> 01:35:26.580
How did it happen?

01:35:26.724 --> 01:35:28.021
It was electrical.

01:35:28.125 --> 01:35:32.027
-The garage door opener went kaput.
-Oh, yeah.

01:35:35.132 --> 01:35:38.590
-Yeah.
-My dad wasn't upset, but my mom was.

01:35:41.239 --> 01:35:42.399
Yeah.

01:35:44.742 --> 01:35:50.578
We lost so many things, I mean,
baby clothes, our photo albums.

01:35:50.715 --> 01:35:51.704
My bike.

01:35:51.816 --> 01:35:56.776
Your bike, important papers,
everything, just...

01:35:58.389 --> 01:36:01.119
We lost a lot. And I remember, I...

01:36:04.795 --> 01:36:09.027
I went to him and I said, you know,
"How can you be so calm?"

01:36:10.067 --> 01:36:13.867
And he said, "Hey, you know,
those are just things, Audrey.

01:36:13.971 --> 01:36:16.735
"Those are just the stuff.
That's just stuff.

01:36:16.841 --> 01:36:19.036
"We still have each other."

01:36:44.101 --> 01:36:45.261
Hi.

01:36:48.139 --> 01:36:49.606
Are you okay?

01:36:53.644 --> 01:36:55.271
This is a list

01:36:59.150 --> 01:37:02.017
of all the things we lost in the fire.

01:37:11.028 --> 01:37:12.461
He's gone.

01:37:19.303 --> 01:37:20.702
He's gone.

01:38:18.429 --> 01:38:22.024
Jerry! Why? Why?

01:38:23.300 --> 01:38:28.932
It's okay. It's okay. It's okay.

01:38:37.114 --> 01:38:39.014
It's gonna be okay.

01:39:59.396 --> 01:40:00.624
Audrey?

01:40:00.731 --> 01:40:03.996
Yeah? I'm back here. In Dory's room.

01:40:05.870 --> 01:40:07.667
Harper told me you wanted to see me.

01:40:07.805 --> 01:40:11.798
Hey, come on. Sit down.

01:40:21.352 --> 01:40:25.118
So I spoke to Kelly.

01:40:27.725 --> 01:40:28.953
And...

01:40:30.694 --> 01:40:34.790
She said that this, you know...

01:40:34.899 --> 01:40:40.963
This facility, or rehab place
really worked for her.

01:40:43.274 --> 01:40:44.400
So...

01:40:47.511 --> 01:40:53.541
Now, I was kind of thinking
that maybe you should go and...

01:40:53.684 --> 01:40:58.553
Audrey, you've already done
enough for me.

01:41:00.191 --> 01:41:02.853
Right. Okay, but, look,
if you're gonna make this about money,

01:41:02.960 --> 01:41:04.689
then I'm gonna be pissed.

01:41:04.795 --> 01:41:06.660
Now, if you wanna make it
about something else,

01:41:06.764 --> 01:41:10.097
I mean, I don't know, whatever,
I'm gonna hate it,

01:41:10.601 --> 01:41:14.537
but, you know, I guess I can accept that.

01:41:31.155 --> 01:41:35.854
You know, Brian used to say something
to the kids all the time.

01:41:37.995 --> 01:41:39.860
"Accept the good."

01:41:44.902 --> 01:41:46.870
Accept the good, Jerry.

01:41:57.648 --> 01:41:59.707
Do they glow in the dark?

01:42:03.754 --> 01:42:06.882
Yeah. They're fluorescent.

01:42:23.173 --> 01:42:24.333
Okay.

01:42:27.378 --> 01:42:29.903
I'll go, but under one condition.

01:42:30.014 --> 01:42:32.847
When I come out, I'm gonna get a job,

01:42:32.983 --> 01:42:38.421
and I'm gonna pay you back, down
to the last penny, and you will take it.

01:42:43.027 --> 01:42:44.324
Promise?

01:43:00.644 --> 01:43:02.669
Hey, Harp.

01:43:02.813 --> 01:43:05.145
Hi, Jerry. Wanna play?

01:43:07.584 --> 01:43:10.382
-Can I talk to you for a second?
-Yeah.

01:43:15.526 --> 01:43:16.857
Okay, here it is.

01:43:18.562 --> 01:43:22.760
I'm gonna be leaving soon.
I'm gonna go to a sort of hospital.

01:43:25.002 --> 01:43:28.165
-For how long?
-Well, I don't know.

01:43:29.373 --> 01:43:33.867
But when I get out, I'm gonna have
my own place and you can come visit.

01:43:37.314 --> 01:43:40.374
You mean
you're not staying here anymore?

01:43:40.517 --> 01:43:41.677
No.

01:43:44.688 --> 01:43:46.212
Why the face?

01:43:47.925 --> 01:43:50.826
That's how it was always gonna be.

01:43:50.928 --> 01:43:54.625
No! You can't just come here
and pretend to be my dad and leave!

01:43:58.002 --> 01:44:02.200
Harper, I never pretended
to be your daddy.

01:44:13.951 --> 01:44:15.248
Where's your sister?

01:44:15.386 --> 01:44:18.412
She locked herself in her room.
She's mad.

01:44:19.623 --> 01:44:22.490
-Why? She's mad at you?
-No. You.

01:44:25.396 --> 01:44:26.727
She's mad at me, huh?

01:44:26.864 --> 01:44:28.889
She doesn't wanna talk to anyone.

01:44:29.033 --> 01:44:32.002
Okay, watch your hand. Scram.

01:44:44.748 --> 01:44:45.772
Jerry!

01:44:46.884 --> 01:44:48.613
Jerry. Man.

01:44:51.055 --> 01:44:53.455
I thought I was gonna miss you.

01:44:56.994 --> 01:44:59.929
-I'm proud of you, man.
-Thank you.

01:45:03.667 --> 01:45:05.794
I'm going back to my wife.

01:45:09.473 --> 01:45:11.941
I'm lonely as fuck in town, man.

01:45:14.111 --> 01:45:15.203
Okay.

01:45:17.481 --> 01:45:18.743
Howard?

01:45:20.918 --> 01:45:22.283
Thank you.

01:45:43.807 --> 01:45:44.899
Harper?

01:45:47.211 --> 01:45:50.647
I want to say goodbye.
Can you take a look at this note?

01:46:05.696 --> 01:46:07.095
I love you.

01:46:26.183 --> 01:46:27.343
Hey.

01:46:45.068 --> 01:46:48.299
Are you gonna be my friend
when you get better?

01:46:50.073 --> 01:46:52.200
I'm gonna be your friend forever.

01:46:52.342 --> 01:46:54.401
Like you were with my dad?

01:46:55.579 --> 01:46:56.705
You bet.

01:46:58.282 --> 01:47:00.375
Now give me a real kiss.

01:47:00.517 --> 01:47:01.882
Good. Okay.

01:47:21.471 --> 01:47:25.066
Wait! Wait!

01:47:30.047 --> 01:47:31.207
Wait!

01:47:32.716 --> 01:47:34.684
Wait! Jerry!

01:47:36.820 --> 01:47:38.117
Hey!

01:48:30.440 --> 01:48:33.568
Hi, my name is Jerry and I'm an addict.

01:48:33.677 --> 01:48:35.770
-Hi, Jerry.
-Hello, Jerry.

01:48:38.215 --> 01:48:41.946
I've been clean for 89 days.

01:48:42.052 --> 01:48:43.986
My mind is clearer,

01:48:48.492 --> 01:48:50.824
and I think it's getting better.

01:48:50.961 --> 01:48:53.521
Every day, a little bit.

01:48:53.664 --> 01:48:56.929
But I wanna talk about this dream
I keep having.

01:48:59.236 --> 01:49:02.763
It always starts
with me stealing silverware.

01:49:02.873 --> 01:49:06.866
<i>Then I go sell it to this guy</i>

01:49:07.010 --> 01:49:10.810
<i>who I used to know
who owned a catering service.</i>

01:49:12.816 --> 01:49:17.617
Then with the money, I go to this place
where I used to buy my drug of choice,

01:49:20.991 --> 01:49:24.051
and he's not around.

01:49:27.030 --> 01:49:29.498
So I go to other spots, right,

01:49:30.600 --> 01:49:35.663
but for some reason, no one is around.

01:49:38.275 --> 01:49:40.971
<i>All of Seattle is dry,</i>

01:49:41.078 --> 01:49:46.015
and then I get that feeling, the dread,

01:49:50.454 --> 01:49:52.149
and I panic.

01:49:56.927 --> 01:49:58.485
And I start running,

01:50:00.731 --> 01:50:03.825
<i>and it's raining, and it gets dark.</i>

01:50:05.869 --> 01:50:10.238
<i>And then I'm in my old apartment,
and I'm thrashing right through it,</i>

01:50:11.375 --> 01:50:14.572
<i>looking for something
I might have stashed away.</i>

01:50:18.115 --> 01:50:20.583
And I think I'm having a seizure.

01:50:23.887 --> 01:50:27.721
And then I find a balloon
hidden in my suitcase.

01:50:49.279 --> 01:50:50.871
So there I am

01:50:53.483 --> 01:50:55.917
with a bag of junk in one hand

01:50:56.953 --> 01:51:00.081
and the money for my next fix
in the other,

01:51:00.190 --> 01:51:03.921
and I feel at total, utter peace.

01:51:13.770 --> 01:51:15.260
And I wake up.

01:51:19.509 --> 01:51:21.238
<i>One day at a time.</i>

01:51:24.381 --> 01:51:26.110
<i>One day at a time.</i>

01:51:32.122 --> 01:51:33.817
One day at a time.

01:51:37.994 --> 01:51:39.757
<i>One day at a time.</i>

01:51:46.970 --> 01:51:48.335
Thank you.

